    <div class="wrapper">
        <%- include('./../_sideNav.ejs') %>

      </nav>
        <!-- page content -->
        <div id="content">
            <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg" style="background-color: black;">
                <button style="padding-left: 30px; padding-bottom: 10px" type="button" id="sidebarCollapse" class="btn btn-info">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-left-to-line"></i>
                    <span></span>
                </button>
            </nav>

            <!--title-->

            <div class="container">

            <!--content-->
            <div style="margin-bottom: 200px; padding: 10px;">
              <!--tag line-->
              <div class="visionTagLine">
                  <p class="subTitleFont" style="padding: 0; font-size: 60px; color: white">ADOPTION</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-2 g-4">
                <div class="col">
                  <div class="card">
                    <img src="/img/a1.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                    <div class="card-body">
                      <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Pumba</a></h2>
                      <div class="card-text">
                        <h6>Male | Adult</h6>
                        <p>Pumba is a very big boy, with the personality to match! A striking red Labrador, with all the personality traits
                            you would expect from the breed, Pumba is funny, friendly and very food-orientated.</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a4.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Popcorn</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Male | Young</h6>
                          <p>Poodle-mix Popcorn is a fluffy ball of joy who wants nothing more than a family to call his own and play with all day.
                            a young dog, Popcorn has lots of energy; he loves the rain and running around in muddy puddles.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a2.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Minnie</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Female | Young</h6>
                          <p>With her unusual tortoiseshell colouring and petite size, she is a very striking cat who adores people and is extremely affectionate.
                            Alongside this, Minnie does have occasional continence issues and struggles to use a litter tray, leading to accidents from time to time.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a3.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Foxy</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Female | Adult</h6>
                          <p>Beautiful Foxy is the biggest sweetie-pie you could meet! Playful and petite, she captures the hearts of all who meet her with
                              her gentle nature and enthusiasm for life. Foxy has a rare disorder which means that she can’t open her mouth properly.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a5.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Finn</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Male | Adult</h6>
                          <p>A striking red Labrador, with all the personality traits you would expect from the breed, Finn is funny,
                              friendly and very food-orientated, and never fails to make us laugh with his antics.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a6.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Libby</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Female | Adult</h6>
                          <p>A beautiful black labrador who was abandoned after sustaining a bad injury to her front leg. Now running around
                              on three legs as well as any four-legged dog, Libby is a strong character who can be very independent.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a7.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Oreo</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Female | Adult</h6>
                          <p>A unique-looking dog, he is very motivated by food, and he likes to play and even “sings” when he’s excited!
                              He is generally quite content in his own company.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a8.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Larry</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Male | Adult</h6>
                          <p>Abandoned due to a skin condition, Larry is a larger-than life character who is desperate to be someone’s best
                              friend! Larry is a typical labrador who loves his food.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a9.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Billu</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Female | Young</h6>
                          <p>A lovely girl whose favourite thing to do is relax, Billu can often be seen lounging around, soaking up the sun
                               in the prime spot. Billu’s gentle nature has made her a firm favourite. </p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a10.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Ginny</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Female | Young</h6>
                          <p>Having not had the easiest life, with a nasty leg fracture, she has proven incredibly resilient and hasn’t let it affect
                              her ability to trust people, showering those that she knows with affection and kisses.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a11.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Arnold</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Male | Adult</h6>
                          <p>People-loving Arnold wants nothing more than to cuddle into you and tries to show you his love by pressing every part
                              of his body into you, seeking out comfort from his favourite people when he is unsure about something.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col">
                    <div class="card">
                      <img src="/img/a12.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/adopt/adoptionForm">Muffin</a></h2>
                        <div class="card-text">
                          <h6>Female | Young</h6>
                          <p>Big fluff ball Muffin just adores being around people and greets everyone with a wagging tail. She is
                              comfortable with being picked up and cuddled, and tries to make friends with everyone.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                </div>


            </div>
            <!-- content-->
        </div>

        <script src="/js/sideNav.js" type="text/JavaScript"></script>
        <div>

        </div>
